    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI have an element in my html file with the ID \"song-template\".\n\nI think the \"ng-template\" within that is triggering Neovim to set the filetype to \"htmlangular\" instead of \"html\", which is messing with some of my LSPs/formatters.\n\nThe regex is [here](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/6780e78b0981f52aec9c4ef96356d3fef3742c9a/runtime/lua/vim/filetype/detect.lua#L851).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nOpen an html file that contains the text \"song-template\".\nThe filetype will be set to \"htmlangular\".\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe filetype should be \"html\".\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS Tahoe 26.4.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nNeovide 0.16.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnix / home-manager",
