            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Fault site is the implicit-anchor asymmetry in the detection alternation:\n\n```\n@\\(if\\|for\\|defer\\|switch\\)\\|\\*\\(ngIf\\|ngFor\\|ngSwitch\\|ngTemplateOutlet\\)\\|ng-template\\|ng-content\n```\n\nThe `@`-prefixed and `*`-prefixed branches self-anchor on punctuation. The element-name branches (`ng-template`, `ng-content`) match anywhere the substring appears, including inside `id`/`class` attribute values. `song-template` contains the literal substring `ng-template` at offset 6, hence the false-positive.\n\nFix is one character per branch: prepend `\\<` so the branches read `\\<ng-template\\|\\<ng-content`. The same lookup table already uses that idiom five lines below at `\\<DTD\\s\\+XHTML\\s`.\n\nWord-boundary trace:\n- `song-template`: positions 0-4 are word chars, no non-word to word transition at the `n`, `\\<ng-template` does not match.\n- `<ng-template>`: position 0 is `<` (non-word), position 1 is `n` (word), `\\<` matches.\n\nVim has the identical code at `runtime/autoload/dist/ft.vim:550` (vim9script form). Per the `needs:vim-patch` label and CONTRIBUTING, the patch lands there first. @dlvandenberg, happy to send the vim/vim PR if useful; otherwise will leave it to you as the original Angular detection author.\n",
            "created_at": "2026-05-14T10:06:57Z",
